                  h3 Testing Sucks
                  p.talk-summary
                    | Testing Sucks. Testable projects don't. With
                    | focus on unit testing with QUnit and DexterJS
                    | (mocking tool) that's a opportunity to reduce
                    | code maintenance in long term projects.
                    br
                    | When testing we may take a longer path, but the
                    | results are a less breaking to unbreakable code.
                    | Doing so, we get more time to spend on new features
                    | instead of fixing bugs without FUD.
